│  Use the advertiser page IDs from the profile map when querying the Meta Ad  │
│  Library — do not search by brand name alone.                                │
│                                                                              │
│  STEP 1 — Call the 'Brand API Data Fetcher' tool with this exact input:      │
│  {"brands": ["Axe", "Old Spice"], "platforms": ["YouTube", "Facebook",       │
│  "TikTok"], "country": "Philippines"}                                        │
│                                                                              │
│  The Meta Ad Library API returns: active ad count, impression ranges         │
│  (min/max), and ad creative text per brand.                                  │
│  NOTE: The 'facebook' platform key covers both Facebook and Instagram —      │
│  Meta Ad Library returns ads running on either surface under the same        │
│  advertiser. Do not create a separate 'instagram' key; treat all Meta ads    │
│  as part of the 'facebook' SOV bucket.                                       │
│                                                                              │
│  STEP 2 — If the API tool returns empty Facebook data (active_ads_found      │
│  missing or platform_data has no Facebook entry), call the 'Paid Ad Library  │
│  Scraper' tool once per brand:                                               │
│    {"brand": "<brand_name>", "country": "Philippines", "platforms":          │
│  ["YouTube", "Facebook"]}                                                    │
│                                                                              │
│  STEP 3 — Call the 'TikTok Ad Library Tool' (tiktok_api_tool) for EACH       │
│  brand:                                                                      │
│    {"brand": "<brand_name>", "country": "Philippines"}                       │
│  Capture:                                                                    │
│    - active_tiktok_ads: count of active ads                                  │
│    - tiktok_ad_start_dates: list of ISO date strings for each active ad      │
│    - tiktok_impressions_min, tiktok_impressions_max: from TikTok EU Ad       │
│  Library unique user reach fields where the brand runs EU campaigns — these  │
│  are the most reliable reach proxies TikTok exposes publicly. For non-EU     │
│  markets this field will be null; record as missing and assign Low           │
│  confidence to the reach bucket signal for TikTok on that brand.             │
│    - tiktok_geo_countries: list of countries where ads are running           │
│  If TikTok API returns no data at all, record zero active ads with           │
│  source_quality='search_fallback' and flag confidence as Low for TikTok. Do  │
│  not halt — proceed with available signals.                                  │
│                                                                              │
│  For ALL platforms, also extract:                                            │
│    - ad_start_dates: list of ISO date strings (for longevity + velocity)     │
│    - geo_countries: list of countries where ads are running                  │
│    - new_ads_last_7d: count of ad IDs with start_date within the last 7      │
│  days (the Creative Velocity signal)                                         │
│                                                                              │
│  Return all collected ad signals combined.                                   │
│  Agent: Feed Ad Capture Agent                                                │
│                                                                              │
│                                                                              │
