│                                                                              │
│  BRANDS IN THIS SCAN: "Axe", "Old Spice"                                     │
│  MARKETS: Philippines                                                        │
│  TODAY'S DATE (for longevity/velocity calculation): 2026-05-26               │
│                                                                              │
│  Analyse the extracted social media data and compute a SHARE-OF-VOICE INDEX  │
│  for each brand. Do NOT compute dollar spend values. Do NOT classify ER as   │
│  a paid signal. Compute SOV for all platforms with equal rigor.              │
│                                                                              │
│  MULTI-MARKET PROCESSING:                                                    │
│  The incoming data is tagged with a 'market' field per snippet and           │
│  platform_data entry. The selected markets are: Philippines.                 │
│  You MUST compute separate SOV records for each market using ONLY that       │
│  market's tagged data.                                                       │
│  Do NOT mix data across markets when computing per-market signals.           │
│  geo_countries from each market's data should be surfaced in the             │
│  'platform_presence' signal — a brand running ads in more countries within   │
│  a market scores higher on Platform Presence.                                │
│  Where a brand has data for multiple markets, the composite_sov and all      │
│  signals are computed independently per market. The 'markets' field in each  │
│  brand record must list which markets the brand appeared in.                 │
│                                                                              │
│  INSTAGRAM NOTE: Instagram data is modelled from the associated Facebook     │
│  Page (Meta Ad Library covers both surfaces). Copy the facebook signals to   │
│  an 'instagram' key and add data_source='modelled_from_facebook'. Do NOT     │
│  fabricate separate Instagram data.                                          │
│                                                                              │
│  TIKTOK SUPPRESSION RULE: After collecting TikTok post data for all brands   │
│  in a given market, count the TOTAL number of TikTok posts detected (across  │
│  all brands). If total TikTok posts < 2 for a market, set                    │
│  tiktok_suppressed=true for that market and exclude TikTok from the          │
│  composite SOV formula (re-weight remaining platforms). This is per-market:  │
│  one market may suppress TikTok while another does not.                      │
│                                                                              │
│  For each brand, produce one SOV record per platform (facebook, instagram    │
│  [modelled], youtube, tiktok):                                               │
│                                                                              │
│  SOV SIGNAL COMPUTATION (normalize each signal 0–100 across all brands):     │
│                                                                              │
│  1. CREATIVE VOLUME SCORE (weight 30% — updated from 35%):                   │
│     Input: active_ads_found per brand per platform                           │
│     Formula: (brand_ads / sum_all_brand_ads_on_platform) × 100               │
│     If no ad data: score = 0, mark source_quality='missing'                  │
│                                                                              │
│  2. CREATIVE VELOCITY SCORE (weight 10%):                                    │
│     Input: new_ads_last_7d per brand (ad IDs with start_date within last 7   │
│  days)                                                                       │
│     Formula: (brand_new_ads_7d / sum_all_brand_new_ads_7d_on_platform) ×     │
│  100                                                                         │
│     If no start_date data: score = 0, mark source_quality='missing'          │
│                                                                              │
│  3. AD LONGEVITY SCORE (weight 15%):                                         │
│     Input: ad_start_dates list per brand                                     │
│     Formula: avg days since earliest start_date → normalize by max across    │
│  brands × 100                                                                │
│     If no start dates: score = 0, mark source_quality='missing'              │
│                                                                              │
│  4. PLATFORM PRESENCE SCORE (weight 15% — replaces Geo Presence):            │
│     Input: number of active platforms per brand (max 4: facebook,            │
│  instagram, youtube, tiktok)                                                 │
│     Formula: (brand_active_platform_count / max_active_platform_count) ×     │
│  100                                                                         │
│     Store result in 'geo_presence_score' field for schema compatibility.     │
│                                                                              │
│  5. REACH BUCKET SCORE (weight 15%):                                         │
│     Input: impressions_min, impressions_max                                  │
│     Map range to tier: <1K=1, 1K–10K=2, 10K–100K=3, >100K=4                  │
│     Normalize: (brand_tier / 4) × 100                                        │
│     If no impression data: score = 0, mark source_quality='missing'          │
│     NOTE: For TikTok, reach data only available from EU Ad Library. If       │
│  brand has no EU campaigns, assign score=0 and Low confidence for this       │
│  signal.                                                                     │
│                                                                              │
│  6. ENGAGEMENT CORROBORATION (weight 15% — updated from 10%):                │
│     Input: er_pct (engagement rate %)                                        │
│     Formula: (brand_er / category_er_benchmark) × 50 (capped at 100)         │
│     Category ER benchmarks — Facebook: General 0.8%, Beauty 1.1%, Food       │
│  1.0%, Finance 0.5%. YouTube: General 2.0%, Beauty 3.0%, Finance 1.5%.       │
│     Secondary signal only — NOT a spend proxy.                               │
│                                                                              │
│  COMPOSITE SOV PER PLATFORM (updated formula):                               │
│     sov_index = (vol×0.30) + (velocity×0.10) + (longevity×0.15) +            │
│  (platform_presence×0.15) + (reach×0.15) + (engagement×0.15)                 │
│     Round to one decimal. Must be in [0, 100].                               │
│                                                                              │
│  PAID/ORGANIC CLASSIFICATION (per post):                                     │
│  ROUTE 1 — Ad Library (primary): If a post_id or ad_id appears in the Meta   │
│  Ad Library, YouTube Ads Transparency, or TikTok Commercial Content Library  │
│  result, classify as post_classification='Paid (Confirmed)',                 │
│  classification_confidence='High'.                                           │
│  ROUTE 2 — Engagement baseline fallback: For posts NOT found in ad           │
│  libraries:                                                                  │
│    - Compute the brand's median engagement (likes+comments+shares+views)     │
│  across all posts on that platform.                                          │
│    - If a post's engagement > 2× median OR in top 10% of brand posts:        │
│  classify as post_classification='Paid (Est.)',                              │
│  classification_confidence='Medium'.                                         │
│    - Otherwise: post_classification='Organic',                               │
│  classification_confidence='High'.                                           │
│  Add these fields to each object in top_posts[]. If no ad library data is    │
│  available for a market (APAC), Route 2 is the live classifier.              │
│                                                                              │
│  CONTENT TYPE CLASSIFICATION (per post):                                     │
│  For each post in top_posts[], determine content_type:                       │
│    - 'brand_say': post from the brand's own account with no external person  │
│  featured                                                                    │
│    - 'sma': brand post featuring an influencer, creator, or partner (detect  │
│  via tags, mentions, or caption references to external persons)              │
│    - 'others_say': post where the PUBLISHER is NOT the brand (third-party    │
│  ad library result where publisher handle ≠ brand handle). Source: Ad        │
│  Library 3rd-party sponsored posts only.                                     │
│  Add content_type field to each top_posts[] object.                          │
│                                                                              │
│  KEYWORDS (per brand, per content type):                                     │
│  From all post captions, extract top-10 keywords for each content type       │
│  (brand_say, sma, others_say). Remove stopwords (the, and, a, to, in, for,   │
│  is, of, on, with, at, by, it, be, as, or, an, we, our, you, your, this,     │
│  that, are, was, will, have, has, can, all, not). Exclude the brand name     │
│  itself. Return as keywords_by_type: {brand_say:[...], sma:[...],            │
│  others_say:[...]}.                                                          │
│                                                                              │
│  TIME-GRAIN DATA:                                                            │
│  If ad_start_dates or post dates are available, emit:                        │
│    by_month: [{period: 'YYYY-MM', composite_sov: <number>}]                  │
│    by_week:  [{period: 'YYYY-WNN', composite_sov: <number>}]                 │
│    by_day:   [{period: 'YYYY-MM-DD', composite_sov: <number>}]               │
│  Only include periods with at least one data point. If insufficient date     │
│  data, emit empty arrays.                                                    │
│                                                                              │
│  CONFIDENCE — BASE TIER (per brand per platform):                            │
│     High:   ≥3 signals with source_quality='primary_api' and score > 0       │
│     Medium: 2 primary_api signals, or 1 primary_api + 1 fallback_scraper     │
│     Low:    ≤1 signal, or only search_fallback                               │
│                                                                              │
│  CROSS-SIGNAL CONSISTENCY CHECK (apply after base tier):                     │
│     Step 1: Rank all brands on Creative Volume (rank 1 = most ads)           │
│     Step 2: Rank all brands on Reach Bucket Score (rank 1 = highest tier)    │
│     Step 3: Compute |creative_volume_rank - reach_bucket_rank| per brand     │
│     Step 4: If divergence > 2 positions: set consistency_flag = true,        │
│  downgrade confidence one tier (High→Medium, Medium→Low)                     │
│     A brand with consistency_flag = true can NEVER have confidence above     │
│  Medium.                                                                     │
│                                                                              │
│  COMPOSITE CROSS-PLATFORM SOV:                                               │
│     Default weights: facebook×0.35 + instagram×0.15 + youtube×0.30 +         │
│  tiktok×0.20                                                                 │
│     If TikTok suppressed (tiktok_posts < 2): facebook×0.44 + instagram×0.19  │
│  + youtube×0.37                                                              │
│     If YouTube missing: facebook×0.50 + instagram×0.21 + tiktok×0.29         │
│     If Facebook/Instagram missing: youtube×0.60 + tiktok×0.40                │
│     composite_confidence = lowest confidence tier across all included        │
│  platforms.                                                                  │
│                                                                              │
│  EXECUTIVE INSIGHTS (generate after all brand SOVs computed):                │
│  For each brand, identify up to 2 strategic observations:                    │
│    - If a brand has high creative_volume but low engagement: note content    │
│  resonance risk                                                              │
│    - If sma posts > 50% of content_type: flag as collaboration-heavy         │
│  strategy                                                                    │
│    - If composite_sov declined across time periods: flag declining momentum  │
│    - If composite_sov > 40%: flag dominant position                          │
│  Return as insights[]: [{brand: '...', text: '...', icon:                    │
│  '📉|📈|🤝|⚠️|👑'}]                                                          │
│                                                                              │
│                                                                              │
